#. <section class="sutta" id="mn148"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn148:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 148"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 148"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn148:0.2"
msgid "Chachakkasutta"
msgstr "Six By Six"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn148:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn148:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn148:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn148:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn148:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:2.1"
msgid ""
"“dhammaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ "
"pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ pakāsessāmi, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I shall teach you the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good "
"in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And I shall "
"reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure, namely,"

msgctxt "mn148:2.2"
msgid "cha chakkāni."
msgstr "the six sets of six."

msgctxt "mn148:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn148:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn148:2.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbāni, cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbāni, "
"cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā, cha phassakāyā veditabbā, cha vedanākāyā "
"veditabbā, cha taṇhākāyā veditabbā."
msgstr ""
"“The six interior sense fields should be understood. The six exterior sense "
"fields should be understood. The six classes of consciousness should be "
"understood. The six classes of contact should be understood. The six classes "
"of feeling should be understood. The six classes of craving should be "
"understood."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:4.1"
msgid "‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn148:4.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn148:4.3"
msgid ""
"Cakkhāyatanaṃ, sotāyatanaṃ, ghānāyatanaṃ, jivhāyatanaṃ, kāyāyatanaṃ, "
"manāyatanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are the sense fields of the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "mn148:4.4"
msgid "‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn148:4.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

msgctxt "mn148:4.6"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ chakkaṃ. (1)"
msgstr "This is the first set of six."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.281"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:5.1"
msgid "‘Cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn148:5.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn148:5.3"
msgid ""
"Rūpāyatanaṃ, saddāyatanaṃ, gandhāyatanaṃ, rasāyatanaṃ, phoṭṭhabbāyatanaṃ, "
"dhammāyatanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are the sense fields of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and "
"thoughts."

msgctxt "mn148:5.4"
msgid "‘Cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn148:5.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

msgctxt "mn148:5.6"
msgid "Idaṃ dutiyaṃ chakkaṃ. (2)"
msgstr "This is the second set of six."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:6.1"
msgid "‘Cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn148:6.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn148:6.3"
msgid "Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.4"
msgid "sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.5"
msgid "ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.6"
msgid "jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.7"
msgid "kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.8"
msgid "manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ."
msgstr "Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts."

msgctxt "mn148:6.9"
msgid "‘Cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn148:6.10"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

msgctxt "mn148:6.11"
msgid "Idaṃ tatiyaṃ chakkaṃ. (3)"
msgstr "This is the third set of six."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:7.1"
msgid "‘Cha phassakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of contact should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn148:7.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn148:7.3"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso;"
msgstr ""
"Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the "
"three is contact."

