msgctxt "mn148:38.1"
msgid ""
"Kāyañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ … pe …."
msgstr "body …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya39"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:39.1"
msgid ""
"“Manañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati "
"phasso, phassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of "
"the three is contact. Contact is a condition for what is felt as pleasant, "
"painful, or neutral."

msgctxt "mn148:39.2"
msgid ""
"So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr ""
"When you experience a pleasant feeling, if you don’t approve, welcome, and "
"keep clinging to it,"

msgctxt "mn148:39.3"
msgid "Tassa rāgānusayo nānuseti."
msgstr "the underlying tendency to greed does not underlie that."

msgctxt "mn148:39.4"
msgid ""
"Dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na socati na kilamati na paridevati na "
"urattāḷiṃ kandati na sammohaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"When you experience a painful feeling, if you don’t sorrow or wail or "
"lament, beating your breast and falling into confusion,"

msgctxt "mn148:39.5"
msgid "Tassa paṭighānusayo nānuseti."
msgstr "the underlying tendency to repulsion does not underlie that."

msgctxt "mn148:39.6"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno tassā vedanāya samudayañca "
"atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When you experience a pleasant feeling, if you truly understand that feeling’"
"s origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape,"

msgctxt "mn148:39.7"
msgid "Tassa avijjānusayo nānuseti."
msgstr "the underlying tendency to ignorance does not underlie that."

msgctxt "mn148:39.8"
msgid ""
"So vata, bhikkhave, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayaṃ pahāya dukkhāya vedanāya "
"paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayaṃ "
"samūhanitvā avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhassantakaro "
"bhavissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Mendicants, after giving up the underlying tendency to desire for pleasant "
"feeling, after dispelling the underlying tendency to repulsion towards "
"painful feeling, after eradicating ignorance in the case of neutral feeling, "
"after giving up ignorance and giving rise to knowledge, it’s totally "
"possible to make an end of suffering in the present life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya40"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.287"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
#. VAR: cakkhusmiṃ → cakkhusmiṃpi (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn148:40.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmiṃ nibbindati, rūpesu "
"nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇe nibbindati, cakkhusamphasse nibbindati, vedanāya "
"nibbindati, taṇhāya nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, "
"sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, feeling, and craving."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya41"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:41.1"
msgid "Sotasmiṃ nibbindati, saddesu nibbindati … pe …"
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the ear …"

msgctxt "mn148:41.2"
msgid "ghānasmiṃ nibbindati, gandhesu nibbindati …"
msgstr "nose …"

msgctxt "mn148:41.3"
msgid "jivhāya nibbindati, rasesu nibbindati …"
msgstr "tongue …"

msgctxt "mn148:41.4"
msgid "kāyasmiṃ nibbindati, phoṭṭhabbesu nibbindati …"
msgstr "body …"

msgctxt "mn148:41.5"
msgid ""
"manasmiṃ nibbindati, dhammesu nibbindati, manoviññāṇe nibbindati, "
"manosamphasse nibbindati, vedanāya nibbindati, taṇhāya nibbindati."
msgstr "mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, feeling, and craving."

msgctxt "mn148:41.6"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When it is freed, they know it is freed."

msgctxt "mn148:41.7"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn148:41.8"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn148:41.9"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn148:41.10"
msgid ""
"Imasmiṃ kho pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne saṭṭhimattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ "
"anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti."
msgstr ""
"And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of sixty mendicants "
"were freed from defilements by not grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn148:41.11"
msgid "Chachakkasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
